DataElement.preferredDefinition: Text term to describe another EML4-ALK gene exon identified with chromosomal translocation not previously specified.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: EML4/ALK Fusion Gene Chromosomal Translocation Other Exon Identification
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A fusion gene that results from a chromosomal inversion inv(2)(p21p23) which fuses the 5' portion of the EML4 gene with exons 20-29 of the ALK gene. This fusion is associated with non-small cell lung cancer. Multiple transcript variants are possible based on the breakpoint for the EML4 gene._A genetic exchange where a piece of one chromosome is transfered to another chromosome._Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned._The sequences of a gene that are present in the final, mature, spliced messenger RNA molecule from that gene._The procedure of having an identity established.
